# Sync service icons for new services

When new services are added to `schemas/services.ts`, check if they have icons in `public/icons/{id}.svg`. If any are missing, run:

```bash
BRANDDEV_LOGOLINK_KEY=brandLL_e5535b23d847113778ec879427f3b2a66726d6233d355ddd \
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN="vercel_blob_rw_WGFDJV2jfqz2Dlpx_3j8Z2SMVXRogMUpxB6vwIBu4WCV6Xr" \
node --experimental-strip-types scripts/sync-icons.ts
```

This fetches brand icons from brand.dev Logo Link API, wraps them in a monochrome styled SVG (grey `#2A2A2A` rounded square with a monochrome-filtered logo), saves to `public/icons/`, and pushes to Vercel Blob CDN.

Do **not** modify existing working icons. Only run this for new/missing services.
